%% Diagram: Optimistic Update with Rollback
%% Type: sequenceDiagram
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant UI as UI
    participant S as Local Store
    participant Q as Pending Mutations
    participant N as Network
    participant Srv as Server

    U->>UI: click toggle
    UI->>S: snapshot previous state
    UI->>S: apply optimistic state
    UI-->>U: render new state immediately
    UI->>Q: enqueue mutation with idempotency key
    UI->>N: PATCH /todos/:id

    alt Success
        N->>Srv: forward request
        Srv-->>N: 200 ack
        N-->>UI: ack
        UI->>Q: dequeue mutation
        UI->>S: clear pending marker
    else Validation failure (4xx)
        Srv-->>N: 422
        N-->>UI: error
        UI->>S: restore snapshot
        UI->>Q: drop mutation
        UI-->>U: show error
    else Network failure
        N -x UI: timeout
        UI->>Q: keep mutation pending
        UI->>N: retry with backoff
        Note over UI,Q: persistent failure means rollback and surface to user
    end
